<subSubSection id="2B2A8770C6087678CFA7EB7A782AE2EB" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="F8F4C56295984BA3A45E6B64B669B2C6" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Blauer Bockshornklee, Schabziegerkraut</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="7E2C8C2CAB766714431AB1B235BEED8E" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" type="description">
<paragraph id="CB1B17D9E70B06FE57097F257FAC3036" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
20-60 cm hoch; zerstreut anliegend behaart oder kahl (auch Kelch und 
<normalizedToken id="D35B64F551B3DC9D2DDC8C44291D5C91" originalValue="Früchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Fruechte</normalizedToken>
). Stengel aufrecht. 
<normalizedToken id="DEEC262A0738702D9765365ECF9D03A3" originalValue="Teilblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Teilblaetter</normalizedToken>
2-5 cm lang, 
<normalizedToken id="0DE63040534E50D70890CA95047F7A28" originalValue="1½" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">11/2</normalizedToken>
-3mal so lang wie breit, das mittlere gestielt. 
<normalizedToken id="8E07DD48F035C12A297BDBD75BBC6123" originalValue="Nebenblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Nebenblaetter</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="1C746220E005352465AEEF29F5BC148B" originalValue="gezähnt" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">gezaehnt</normalizedToken>
. 
<emphasis id="916593B54F60E2F42CD12FA5E44CE263" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<normalizedToken id="7E9F239E4D7BDBEF515ACA06BC6B24CF" originalValue="Blüten" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Blueten</normalizedToken>
zahlreich in lang gestielten, kurzen, kopfartigen Trauben.
</emphasis>
Kelch etwa 
<normalizedToken id="5CE9EDF2EAC09F5C5A0005BB7FC15A02" originalValue="½" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">1/2</normalizedToken>
so lang wie die Krone. 
<emphasis id="5FE28C857C82DD20AA022FB9C9DA1D02" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
Krone 5-7 mm lang, hellblau. Frucht 
<normalizedToken id="CAEA05DC59752A5D1B86F1A4D67F72B1" originalValue="eiförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">eifoermig</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="8CFD188B5FF4BE9606A1BDFE87D0368E" originalValue="geschnäbelt" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">geschnaebelt</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="FCB455DEFC3CEBF4B6C790600BE79317" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Schnabel etwa 2 mm lang</emphasis>
), 
<emphasis id="C8CEF8DB3224E9A2FFBC5F11233159D8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">gerade, mit dem Schnabel zusammen 5-7 mm lang</emphasis>
und 2-3 mm dick. Samen zu 1-2, 
<normalizedToken id="94F4291A6309B37FFA41416151C6BF71" originalValue="eiförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">eifoermig</normalizedToken>
, sehr fein warzig, 1,5-2 mm lang. - 
<normalizedToken id="4599230525E23683F0137CA1776B782F" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B12391638CBBBD9D25FB5FB063097205" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis id="47CB3E58A01396EE82061361F7BB70F7" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="46DA242DADD3359703204C3862CEA34B" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">16:</emphasis>
Material aus Kulturen (Fryer 1930, Senn 1938, Coutinho und Santos 1943).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="372BD09846DAA8939EAC1849B347DB14" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis id="CA23FF4F6B551B445FD2DA2FDCCB7AE0" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin. Trockene, lockere, 
<normalizedToken id="A3814B1B735E38AB939FE06CD10A4BA6" originalValue="nährstoffreiche" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">naehrstoffreiche</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="41B8D6BAB6A8B67C6430EEA5E3FD623F" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Boeden</normalizedToken>
in 
<normalizedToken id="01B4D94AD3170183847E7C822096F2FE" originalValue="wärmeren" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">waermeren</normalizedToken>
Lagen. 
<normalizedToken id="2E3B0C05B79B01067591643C8CBA723A" originalValue="Äcker" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Aecker</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="2654118745B82B167D2039099CA6A8DA" originalValue="Schuttplätze" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Schuttplaetze</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E95B10EC7175B00E9CF383FE3F0A7439" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis id="C2A5E97744B0579EB97EB411FC89C0E9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Verbreitung.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="61F595A21017C622A59BA4579E5FF03B" originalValue="Ursprünglich" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Urspruenglich</normalizedToken>
wahrscheinlich 
<emphasis id="690F8EAC61304534F84C39A9B1614089" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<normalizedToken id="5A2644180A3BD6AA68EDBF3B039900A0" originalValue="osteuropäische" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">osteuropaeische</normalizedToken>
Pflanze.
</emphasis>
- Im Gebiet besonders in den Kantonen Schwyz und Glarus gelegentlich angebaut (liefert das Aroma 
<normalizedToken id="DE0E04B7A5D94D6EED4C57F1EC2E4ED8" originalValue="für" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">fuer</normalizedToken>
Schabzieger), selten verwildert.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8C4D091C85C063EEFC771062C65FE4B0" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis id="BA8EA9A1E8EB4C042852DBD389B7F7FA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Bemerkungen.</emphasis>
Die nahe verwandte 
<emphasis id="5C052C60AB09009AB72E0CB6D2D28AEC" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">
<normalizedToken id="A4C201BD5C18B57305FCA75901449CAB" originalValue="osteuropäisch-westasiatische" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">osteuropaeisch-westasiatische</normalizedToken>
Steppenpflanze 
<taxonomicName id="F814B867D4771DC742DF43DE488E8C1E" authority="(Bess.) Rchb." authorityName="Rchb." baseAuthorityName="Bess." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cytisus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procumbens">T. procumbens (Bess.) Rchb.</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
tritt gelegentlich adventiv auf und unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="A4686BEDE6DEE6AF7F1F12ADB327A717" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Trigonella" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="null" pageNumber="530" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coerulea">
<emphasis id="124DF352C6F2AE8A2ED9FCEC20005033" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">T. coerulea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
besonders durch niederliegende oder bogig aufsteigende Stengel und durch 1-3 cm lange, 3-5mal so lange wie breite 
<normalizedToken id="57879F3B187FF6CFEBE4C8BB341D5DEE" originalValue="Teilblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="530">Teilblaetter</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
